{
  "texts": [
    "• appropriate human oversight measures to minimise risk",
    "• high level of robustness, security and accuracy.",
    "Operators of high-risk AI systems need to undergo a conformity assessment procedure conducted by competent institutions and, if needed, implement corrective actions before putting the system into service.",
    "Each member state has to designate or establish at least one national competent authority to serve as the national supervisory authority, the notifying authority and the market surveillance authority.",
    "However, most GAI applications, such as chatbots, will probably be categorised as \"limited risk\" AI systems, which are primarily subject to transparency obligations."
  ]
}